Excoecaria agallocha

   [1059.jpg]
    Authority
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Euphorbiales:Euphorbiaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names feta'anu, mangrove
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 1059

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A moderate sized evergreen or briefly deciduous bushy tree reaching a
   height of 10-30 m.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   Blinding tree, Milkwood, Gengwa, Geor, Geria, Geva, Gewa, Suran,
   Surund, Tilai, Thilla, Tayaw, Kayaw.
   FURTHER INF
   The tree exudes a very acrid poisonous juice, particularly from the
   fresh cortex when cut, which raises blisters on the skin and is
   injurious to the eyes of wood-cutters, whence the name 'blinding tree'.
   The latex is used for fish poison. It occurs along the coast and around
   tidal creeks at elevations between sea level and 400 m. It thrives in
   areas with a relative humidity between 70-90%. Photosynthesis pathway
   C3.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Troup R 1921 pp 844-845 [USE, LIMITS, DRA, SAL]
   Tomlinson P 1986 pp 238 [SAL]
   Aronson J 1989 pp 61 [SAL]
   Paijmans K 1976 pp 35
   Zabala N 1990 pp 47-49 [DRA, SAL, TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, USE]

